This paper deals with the distribution of incomes earned from publishing papers, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of the Impact Factor-based ranking journal as a criteria for credit allocation also suggests a connection to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY). Additionally, the Harmonic Credit Index mentioned in the paper may be related to signal processing (cs.SI).
